<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74a60035-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s153903"><num value="153903">§ 153903.</num><heading> Powers</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a60036-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s153903/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> adopt a constitution and bylaws;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a60037-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s153903/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> adopt a seal; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id74a60038-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s153903/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> hold real and personal property in the United States, but only to the extent necessary to carry out the purposes of the corporation and only in an amount not more than $50,000.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id74a60039-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1431">112 Stat. 1431</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
